sudo ln -sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Berlin /etc/localtime


Create a Template File: Let's say you have a template file template.txt with the following content:

Hello, my name is {{NAME}}.
I am {{AGE}} years old.
Create a Bash Script: Create a bash script replace_variables.sh to replace the placeholders with actual values:

bash
#!/bin/bash

# Define the variables
NAME="John"
AGE="30"

# Use sed to replace the placeholders in the template file
sed -e "s/{{NAME}}/$NAME/g" -e "s/{{AGE}}/$AGE/g" template.txt > 
